Reason I ask is that I'm in a guild that has thusfar always thrived to push itself to kill mobs with low numbers.<br>
Last friday tho part of the guild was involved in a try to kill it with about 120 people and it is basicly tearing our guild apart.<br>
Am I wrong in my assumption that you don't need 100+ people to kill it??<br>
Thanks for your replies. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://&quot;http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=180165&quot;">Crayno Wolffang,Barbarian Overlord</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://ringdernibelungen.de/">Ring der Nibelungen</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=aakla2>aakla2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>/cons RED</span><br>  Posts: 343<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/24/03 4:22 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://pages.prodigy.net/mikekling/Smilies/babytumbleI.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: MB in POI</span><hr size=1> you dont need that much. <br>
<br>
I would say 30-40 6-6-20 or 6-6-30<br>
<br>
it all depends on how good your guild is and your resists.<br>
<br>
think we've done it with 50ish no problems.<br>
<br>
