<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://images.allposters.com/images/54/039_15016.jpg">Barbarian</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> Overlord <br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.realpoor.com">Tarew Marr</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=chidder>Chidder</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/24/03 11:54 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: MB in POI</span><hr size=1> behemoth has 100k hp i am told so every 1k damage is 1% of health  so 1 wizard can do atleast 10k damage pretty easy........ so it should be pretty simple<br>
<br>
My guild got 1 try got him  to 40% with l ike 65-70 but  our problem was not the tank or anyone dieing someone let spiders get by=( but his health drops really really fast <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=1ludor>1Ludor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 130<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/24/03 12:07 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: MB in POI</span><hr size=1> it IS a zerg fight, invite a second guild with you if need be. your guild should be buying clerics the 2500 group heal if they dont got it. group heals are the mana sink though, you should be able to handle the spiders with decent enchanters, really got as much time to kill him as you can cast that group heal. if you are just missing a cleric or two or any other class, invite some along.../w all 65 cleric... <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=577575&amp;resize=true" target="top">Ludor Sheolbane</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.bladesoflaw.org">Blades of Law</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=farlanderb>FarlanderB</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 91<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/24/03 12:27 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: MB in POI</span><hr size=1> Don't let your clerics Mass Group Buff before the fight. Let them click MGB on and use their group heal over time spells. It's a LOT (and I mean LOT) of aggro. Save the AE taunts for after this.. but it keeps your people up. <p>Veteran Farlander - 65 Overlord<br>
Fainel - 38 Enchanter<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.guild-legerdemain.com">Legerdemain</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=garorm@thesteelwarrior>garorm</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.seretogis.org/files/linkables/ogrechief.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 38<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/26/03 2:37 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.seretogis.org/files/linkables/ogrechief.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: MB in POI</span><hr size=1> &quot;you should be able to handle the spiders with decent enchanters&quot;<br>
<br>
Last I checked, mezzing a spider will cause another to immediately spawn, which is bad. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=339348" target="top">Veteran Garzok</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> - Overlord of  <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.torrentvz.com" target="top">Torrent</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.seretogis.org/files/linkables/garzok - overlord sig.png" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=solinarinnoruuk>Solinar Innoruuk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>/cons RED</span><br>  Posts: 327<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/26/03 3:00 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: MB in POI</span><hr size=1> Lotta misinformation here.<br>
<br>
Spiders will continue to spawn, regardless of whether they are killed, mezzed or tank mezzed.  Some guilds leave people killing spiders, other have enchanters mez them for the duration of the fight.<br>
<br>
The only heal that can be MGB is Etheral Elixer as it is considered a regen type short lasting group buff rather than a heal.  It is almost no aggro to MGB Etheral Elixer.  &quot;Word of&quot; group heals do however still cause massive aggro. Also low HP aggro will be bad in this fight, expect him to bounce around alot.<br>
<br>
This fight can also be won with a war of attrition as opposed to brute force.  We once tried him with 45ish people and had 5ish at each corner killing adds.  That left 25 people on Behemoth himself.  We very quickly got him to 50% and then the DPS folks died.<br>
<br>
At around 40% life, I did a /who GUILD and quickly saw that the only ones left on behemoth were 4 clerics me bard and a rogue.  4 clerics bard and I were all grouped so we were resisting AEs. The rogue had good resist gear and was catching AE resist as well from the bard.  We worked Behemoth down to 1% when both I and the rogue died. Bard got the killing blow heh.<br>
<br>
So you can do behemoth himself with very low numbers if your resist is good since his melee output is ass. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=odiussilvertongue>OdiusSilvertongue</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 75<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/28/03 1:48 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: MB in POI</span><hr size=1> Was wondering if anyone had any tips/hints on killing Behemoth with low healers/priests, no bards for resists, and the wonderful gas leak AE.  Without a number of clerics how do people do healing against an AE that even if you resist it still knocks you back every 6 seconds?  Are we missing some fast cast (sub 6 second) heals that non cleric priests have that could effectively heal against the AE in this encounter?<br>
<br>
This combination of attributes seems to be what we get most of the we find Behemoth up.  Normally get him to around 8-10% health left but half the dmg is done when 75% of our force/dps is dead.<br>
<br>
Also was hoping someone could verfiy I am understanding the gas leak AE correctly.  As I understand it it does 900dmg per tick (like all of his AE's) with a 120second recast time, all taken from Lucy.  Lucy also shows a duration of 1 to 3 ticks.  The question is in terms of the recast (20 ticks between casts) and duration (max of 3 ticks?) this would mean there are 17 ticks or 1 min and 45 seconds that AE shouldn't be doing anything.  Everyfight we have had with Behemoth the AE was felt consistent throughout the fight, but since I didn't bother to log it I can not prove otherwise.   <p><B><a href= http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=81233><FONT SIZE="-1">Vladimoir</a></FONT></B>
